These are generic files to run daqd, nds, caRepeater on Debian8, while still using old log file directories.

Install bin/* into /bin
Install etc/systemd/* to /etc/systemd
Install etc/systemd/system/* to /etc/systemd/system

You control things by the config files in /etc/systemd
daqd.conf - defines daq
 - set DAQ_DC_FLAG to 1 on frame-builders/data-concentrators, to 0 otherwise
DAQ_DC_FLAG=0
DAQ_TARGET_DIR=/opt/rtcds/tst/x2/target/x2daqfw0
DAQ_LOG_DIR=/opt/rtcds/tst/x2/target/x2daqfw0/logs

nds.conf - defined nds on NDS servers
NDS_TARGET_DIR=/opt/rtcds/tst/x2/target/x2daqnds0
NDS_LOG_DIR=/opt/rtcds/tst/x2/target/x2daqnds0/logs

once placed, you can enable/start with usual 'systemd' commands
